I just started downloading Subnautica earlier, how is it?
It is masterful in its use of tension and suspense.
Word of advice: Hull reinforcement ASAP. And for goodness' sake, unless there's no other choice, stay away from the Dunes, Mountains and Crash Zones, as those are the Reaper's favourite places.
But yes, it is very scary.
Subnautica is a game I want to play
It is beautiful, immersive, and mystifying
But at the same time braves the depths of the human psyche to terrify us in familiar and ancient ways.
Also, if you want a good time, go outside the bounds of the game map
